players to the mod in charge of scheduling. On that player list include whether the players are guilded or indy. After a month or so, total the guilded and indy numbers to see which there are more of. If its 5/1 or 1/1 then make the reservation system based on that ratio. Yes not everyone will be happy, but that is the only way to let the Brell &quot;community &quot; speak.<br>
<br>
 You cant rely on polls or posts here to be accurate. So let the community speak through its actions, those actions being the players going on these raids. If necessary change the ratio if the actual player ratio changes. <br>
<br>
  I dont want to see it go FFA before I can even go on one of the raids. I see this as the only fair way to determine the scheduling.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp.<br>
<br>
Krispin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uveranonwindseeker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veranon Windseeker</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://hem.passagen.se/trench/sr/icon1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of the North [Admin]</span><br>  Posts: 1204<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/6/01 2:50:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if?</span><hr size=1> that would most likely end up as guilds not inviting indies for a month so they would get more raids in the future... <p><a href=http://sr.amiga.tm/cgi-bin/members.cgi?show=Veranon target=_document >
<img src=http://hem.passagen.se/trench/sr/squeeze.gif border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urealmsman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>realmsman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/6/01 9:13:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if?</span><hr size=1> The other side of the coin, that would mean no indy's would invite guilded for a month so they would get more reservations in the future. Hmmmmmm .. what is your point then, Veranon. <br>
<br>
 This is just the offering of a solution rather than just complaining about it. I personally know one person who posts on this board under two different names, yes even to the same topic. With that going on how can we rely on these boards for accurate voting or polls? I saw the phrase  &quot; one voice, one vote&quot; in another post. How can we be sure that one of those voices is the 3rd or 4th voice of just one person? You have to rely on integrity and trust. <br>
<br>
The solution I offer you have to rely on integrity and trust. You have to trust that your friends that are hosting the raid, have the integrity to still invite you whether you or they are guilded or indy. Walk into any store, cafe, etc.. you will more than likely see a sign that says &quot;we reserve the right to refuse service to anyone&quot;, if I were hosting a raid, I would go by the same statement. Few things in this game really matter, the friendships that develop really do matter. The reputation that you create for yourself ingame or on the board matter. I dont care how good someone thinks another player is, if they have wronged me or my friends I wont group with them. If someone talks down about someone that I think to be good, I voice my opinion of that person. <br>
<br>
I'm still to low to go on the raids, but Im trying to offer a solution that is equitable to all. Yes people will be unhappy, all that means is they didn't get what they wanted. What is best for the most is what I want. If that means indy's get more raids then befriend soem indy's or become the best  so that you are wanted on their raids. If that means that guildies get more raids, then befriend some guildies or become the best  so that you are wanted on their raids.<br>
<br>
Most important step up to the plate and try to hit the ball, instead of sitting back and complaining about the pitches, the rules , and the other batters that are trying to hit the ball. Make a difference.<br>
<br>
Krispin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch! [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1885<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/7/01 7:06:42 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if?</span><hr size=1> I defy any Indy person to pull of an entire planar raid made up of only unguilded people.  It's not going to happen. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="400" height="175"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessage?topicID=1745.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.showMessage?topicID=1730.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.threadControl?topicID=1742.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1742.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisplanesraids.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1742.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.j